title: Sulawesi swiftlet
text:
The Sulawesi swiftlet ("Aerodramus sororum") is a species of <a href="Swift%20%28bird%29">swift</a> in the family <a href="Apodidae">Apodidae</a>.
It is <a href="Endemism">endemic</a> to <a href="Sulawesi">Sulawesi</a>. It used to be considered a subspecies of the <a href="Moluccan%20swiftlet">Moluccan swiftlet</a>.
Its natural <a href="habitat">habitat</a>s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland <a href="forest">forest</a>s and subtropical or tropical moist <a href="montane%20forest">montane forest</a>s.
